Pie Chart¶

In [12]:
labels = ['Ozone' , 'Solar Radiation', 'Wind','Temperature']
sizes = [A['Ozone'].mean(), A['Solar.R'].mean(), A['Wind'].mean(),A['Temp'].mean()]
colors = ['blue', 'orange','purple','red']
explode = (0.5,0,0,0)
plt.pie(sizes, explode=explode,labels=labels, colors=colors,autopct = '%1.1f%%',shadow=True, startangle=150)
plt.title('Average Data')
plt.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Replace empty strings with NaN
A.replace(' ', float('nan'), inplace=True)

# Drop rows with missing values
A.dropna(inplace=True)

# Calculate correlation matrix
corr = A.corr()

# Plot heatmap
sns.heatmap(corr, annot=True)
plt.show()
